SHG and LMO symmetry of 58 Black-White magnetic point groups

Notation:

(1) MPG: magnetic point group, LMO: linear magneto-optic effect.

(2) MPG M0=S0+T(G0−S0)=S0+R′S0, where G0 is the isomorphism group, and S0 is the invariant subgroup of point group G0 (s=g/2, s and g are the order of group S0 and G0 respectively).

(3) the subscript number of SHG tensor means the independent element number.

(4) The symmetry of LMO effect refer the LMO table.

Note: If the table is not fully displayed, please jump to the bottom and slide the display bar left and right.
